Step-by-step setup
1) Create a new Freestyle project
Open Jenkins → click New Item
Enter a name (example: welcome-job)
Select Freestyle project
Click OK

2) Add a String Parameter
Inside the job:
Scroll to This project is parameterized
Check the box
Click Add Parameter → String Parameter
Fill in:
Name: STUDENT_NAME
Default Value: Noshank (or leave empty)
Description: Enter your name

3) Add a build step
Scroll to Build → Add build step → Execute Windows batch command
command:
echo Hello %STUDENT_NAME%, Welcome to Jenkins!

4) Save and Build the job
Click Build with Parameters, enter a name, and run it.
You’ll see output like:
Hello Noshank, Welcome to Jenkins!
